This paper deals with the development of modular proof theory and automated reasoning for abstract separation logics, which are used for reasoning about programs that manipulate resources such as memory locations. This topic is closely related to several areas of computer science, including logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
